title: [climbing] Dosage Vol 4
description:
Cover: http://media.rei.com/media/994366.jpg

The Dosage climbing film series is the most popular look at all forms of modern climbing, bouldering, trad or sport.

Dosage vol IV, the fourth climbing film in the series makes the greatest climbs of the year come alive before your eyes. Tommy Caldwell makes big wall freeclimbing history in Yosemite, with his linkup of El CapitanÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¯Ã‚Â¿Ã‚Â½ÃƒÂ¯Ã‚Â¿Ã‚Â½s The Nose (5.14a) and Freerider (5.12d), for 6,000 feet of climbing in under 24 hours. Dave Graham and Chris Sharma open impossible boulders in Ticino, Switzerland and Hueco Tanks, Texas, then focus their power on a new breed of hybrid sport routes, with the first ascents of Coup de Grace (5.15a, Ticino) and Dreamcatcher (5.14d, Squamish, BC). And Lisa Rands summons her strength and masters her fear on the first female ascent of the dangerous UK grit route Gaia (E8).

Dosage IV combines top-level action with beautiful cinematography and a mind-expanding soundtrack to create an immersive climbing experience so real it feels like a dream....
